AI-driven Threat Detection Basics
Objectives
By the end of this lab, students will be able to:

• Implement basic anomaly detection algorithms for security log analysis • Create automated alert mechanisms for suspicious activities • Build machine learning models for threat classification • Apply statistical methods to identify unusual patterns in system logs • Configure real-time monitoring systems for cybersecurity applications

Prerequisites
Before starting this lab, students should have:

• Basic Python programming skills (functions, loops, file I/O) • Familiarity with Linux command line operations • Understanding of basic statistics (mean, standard deviation) • Basic knowledge of log file formats

Lab Environment
This lab uses a single Linux machine with:

• Ubuntu 20.04 LTS or newer • Python 3.8+ with pip • Pre-installed text editors (nano, vim) • Network connectivity for package installation

Note: Click "Start Lab" to access your pre-configured cloud machine.

