Troubleshooting Tips
Issue: ModuleNotFoundError for pandas or sklearn

Solution: Ensure packages are installed: pip3 install pandas numpy scikit-learn
Issue: Log file not found errors

Solution: Verify you're in the correct directory and log file exists: ls -la logs/
Issue: Real-time monitor not detecting new entries

Solution: Ensure log file is being appended to (not overwritten) and monitor has read permissions
Issue: ML models show poor performance

Solution: Generate more diverse log data with better separation between normal and suspicious activities. Adjust feature engineering to capture more relevant patterns.
Conclusion
This lab introduced fundamental concepts of AI-driven threat detection in cybersecurity. You implemented statistical anomaly detection methods, created real-time monitoring systems, and built machine learning models for automated threat classification. These techniques form the foundation of modern Security Information and Event Management (SIEM) systems.

Key Takeaways:

Statistical methods (mean, standard deviation) effectively detect outliers in log data
Real-time monitoring requires efficient file reading and pattern matching
Machine learning models can learn complex threat patterns from labeled data
Feature engineering is critical for ML model performance in security applications
Combining multiple detection methods (statistical + ML) improves overall accuracy
Next Steps: Explore advanced techniques like deep learning for sequence analysis, integrate with real SIEM platforms, or implement distributed log processing for large-scale systems.
